caption: Phenomenal menu during quarantine -- it keeps well on the drive home, and it has such depth of flavor and richness that I was scraping my plate for every last bit. Can't wait to go back and try more!

I absolutely loved this place. The service is great and polite, the food actually has flavor and it’s fresh! I had the avocado toast Benedict if I remember the name correctly and the blueberry pancakes and it was sooooo fresh and so tasty! I also had the pumpkin spice latte and it was 💯
The menu and service were beyond our expectations. We surely enjoyed the environment of this restaurant. Superb place to take the family out for lunch.

We've been going to Obelisk for over 10 years. It is our go-to special occasion restaurant. It's a small, relaxed restaurant where the menus are hand-made and they regularly just keep bringing you delicious food. I trust that everything I will eat there will be carefully prepared and delicious. As such, I can always feel confident trying new items. The bread and cheese are fantastic and come from a common serving table in the middle of the restaurant. It's not cheap, but you pay for consistency and quality. If we haven't seen friends for a while and they're only in town for a short time, we'll take them here. You can enjoy a 2-hour meal that never feels rushed and is full of new incredible dishes to talk about.

In non-pandemic times, this is a gem of a restaurant for a date night or another special occasion out—truly excellent, creative Italian food, rarely the same menu twice, served as a relaxed tasting menu.  Nowadays, they're serving take-out.  We are delighted to have been able to have their pescatarian Christmas Eve feast to celebrate the hoilday.  Everything was perfectly packaged and lost little in translation to our dining room table at home, from the wine pairings that fit perfectly (but I'd never have considered—Barolo with swordfish) to the trademark array of antipasti to the panforte dessert.  You should order take-out from here, both to support a neighborhood institution and just because it's delicious.  We will be doing so again.
Excellent location for tasty Italian food. filled me up in no time.

This is one of the best takeout experiences in DC - a 2020 staple for us. They constantly change the menu (non-veg and veg) and the trademark Obelisk mix of creative and classic compels us to try one or both almost every week. The food is always impeccable, whether it's the latest seasonal dish or a classic (like the bread and burrata - the only part of the menu that never changes, nor should it, because it is perfect and you can never have enough). Prices include service and it's a good value for the high quality ingredients. The "worst" dish we've had since they reopened has still been great-to-excellent; the best have been transcendental, even at home. We often split one menu, adding 1-2 a la carte items to round it out. This is the right amount of food to keep trying their new offerings each week and avoid overeating, but sometimes tests our love for each other as it's tempting to eat each entire delectable dish for yourself! (Tip: Eat the hot dishes first and save the cold ones for last, even if that means partially inverting the menu.) A la carte items also make a great lunch. The sandwiches are petite but so, so tasty (I hope they bring back the egg and homemade sausage soon!) and round out well with a soup or salad, and the lasagna is fantastic (tip: request to buy it cold if you want to heat it yourself the next day).  Pre-COVID, this was also a lovely experience for in-person dining. It's a given that the food will be incredible. The service was also fantastic, the venue intimate, the meals leisurely-paced and delightful. We can't wait to go back in person when it's safe!

My husband and I have been long-time patrons of this stellar Italian restaurant. They are now offering a pre fixe meal to-go (one regular, one vegetarian-both with their must eat homemade burrata) and an a la carte menu as well. We tried both the regular and vegetarian and they were absolutely delicious. We also picked a few items off the a l carte- all scrumptious and so well priced. I highly recommend Obelisk for a great at home date covid-era night...or any night! Next best thing to eating in their restaurant.
Fantastic small restaurant focused on their prix fixe 5 course dinner. Excellent service and wine program. A very special place.
Delicious food.
Favorite Italian restaurant in DC. Food and service on point.
Incredible experience for my birthday!
Cozy setting, no nonsense food, extremely knowledgeable staff. Make sure to choose to combine the set menu with the wine pairing. You will truly be in for a treat.
Perfection!

Great low key ambience. Our server was heroic in being a solo on a night when more people showed than expected. She gave us great guidance on the menu and wines while holding down the fort with four or five tables. The menu offered just enough choices and the three of us were all happy. The black bass was perfectly prepared, not overcooked. The duck breast was likewise perfectly cooked, and as generous a portion as we have seen anywhere. The pasta course offered variety -- I had a ravioli with watercress and walnuts; my wife and guest had scallops that were large, tender and perfectly cooked. The wine (a Brunello di Montalcino) perfectly bridged our main courses.  We last were at Obelisk for our third or fourth wedding anniversary, around 30 years ago. The restaurant remains a gem.

This is an annual spot for us. It's an intimate space where we thoroughly enjoy the experience from the minute we walk into the door. The menu is simple and the food well executed. Everyone there is lovely.
This is the most amazing place ! the service exceptional. the food is amazing. We are pescatarian and the made sure they took care of our needs .
Simple, yet elegant Italian cuisine, with attentive service in a townhouse setting.
Went here for a 5 year anniversary.. totally worth the unique experience however I would not recommend ordering the squab. It was too difficult to eat.
Great service, good no-fuss Italian food.

Truly a fabulous dining experience.  From the appetizers to the dessert everything was fantastic.  I don't particularly like lamb but they served a lamb appetizer that was mind blowing.  We also enjoyed the wine pairing that really elevated all of the food. In some ways I was lucky in that they happened to be serving a number of my favorite foods the night I went (risotto balls, burratta, bruschetta, wagyu steak).  Regardless of that, Highly recommend.
Amazing mood and food! Worth every penny.

This place was recommended by a waiter at another restaurant who recognized we're foodies... And it did not disappoint!  Then menu is hand-written every day, based on local ingredients and what's available. And every course is absolutely perfect! The wine pairings were on point as well! The staff is very friendly and so helpful.  This is definitely a little-known secret in DC, but 100% worth checking out! Next time I'm in town, this will definitely be a place I come back to!

This exquisite dining location offers up an intimate dining experience. The servers are very friendly and knowledgeable about the menu and wine offerings. The food itself is a perfect selection of courses that changes often.  I took my fiancée (then girlfriend) here on a Saturday evening for a Valentine's Day meal and we had an excellent evening together, enjoying a lengthy dinner that offered enough time between courses to enjoy conversation and the ambiance.

I had an amazing experience from beginning to end. I got all courses along with the wine pairings, everything was good. It was a great opportunity to get out of my comfort zone and try new things as well.

Wow.. food was so amazing! Great chef! The dishes pair perfectly with wine. 2-3 hour course. Worth the wait. I tasted like 12 different dishes not sure exact number, but felt like 12. Service was A+++. Would definitely come back. Every penny and wait worth it.

(10 stars) Obelisk is an experience. It's quaint and personal. There are 3 at the back of the house (the chef, sous chef and a dishwasher) and 2 in front. The women in front are knowledgeable in every aspect and so friendly and willing to share. There is zero pretense here. It's about the food, the wine and the experience. The wine list is very approachable although we decided on pairings. The menu is ever changing to provide a new experience each time. We will make this a regular (out of the way) stop.
Fantastic multicourse meal in an adorable little row house. Every dish was creative and it's really impressive how much is much made fresh in-house, including the butter! Will definitely be back.

An incredible experience. The restaurant itself, the staff, and especially the food far exceeded (our already high) expectations. Everything is made in-house and it shows. Would highly recommend for a high-level dining experience.

In the chaos of the possible shooter during DC pride the workers and owners allowed us (people attending the parade to feel safe). I want to thank you all from the bottom of my heart for being a safe place to shelter in. Forever will support this establishment for just treating us as human beings in the time of need. A true blessing indeed. Thank you
Amazing food and service with well matched wines.

Excellent, personable service, creating a relaxed dining experience. Dinner was 2 hours and 45 minutes but felt perfectly paced. Everything, from the ridiculously delicious sourdough to the gently tart fruit jellies served with the check, was handmade on premises and tasted like it.  Would absolutely rush back.
expensive but very good, lovely setting
Amazing food and dining experience! No set menu. What they serve is different every day depending on what is fresh! Each course was unique and delicious!
Delicious! They put so much care into the food. Eating here really made our evening special.
Came for an anniversary dinner and was not disappointed! I especially liked the ravioli.

The real thing. From A to Z, Obelisk is something you are going to love. Might not be cheap, so prepare some $$$, but know you are going to get one of the best food in D.C. I will not describe one dish, since they were all amazing. 5 stars with no doubt.

First and foremost, expect a 3 hr meal. I don't need it to be rushed but there was way too much waiting on the next course.  -Service was fantastic, very friendly. -Wine pairing, not worth it to me. I didn't care for any of the wines. 2-3oz each. Only 1 of the 2 of us got the pairing luckily. -Food was honestly disappointing. There was not one item I would say "be sure to eat ....." The Gnocchi was bland, suckling pig was good, but nothing you couldn't have elsewhere.  All in all it's not that the place is bad, but you could have food of similar quality for better price elsewhere. We were disappointed.

Without question one of the great restaurants, not just in DC but in the United States. The staff and the food are both creative, elegant, and kind. At my last dinner there, a friend said "It's like watching fireworks, but you can eat them."

Always a pleasure to see want delicious mezo courses at chef sends out between the fixed menu. We've been going here for years for special occasions as a family and have never been anything but delighted.

Once you find the door (up the stairs!) you're transported into a cozy and classy dining room. Great price for an amazing 5 course dinner. Bread sticks are out of this world. The antipasti course was phenomenal. The butterscotch custard was irresistible. 5/5 would recommend.
Remarkable food, professional service. Plan at least 2 hours for dinner.  Even if you think something on the menu isn't something you typically like,  give it a try here.  It's just masterful.
Very upscale Italian food. Prefix menu only, dinner takes about three hours. Great food, great wine, but very expensive. Expect to spend about $200 per person.
Exceptional!

Amazing amazing dinner ,be prepared to spend at least 2 hours eating! The set menu was varied and allowed us to try a variety of dishes, ravioli, crab soup, pork chops, chicken ,chocolate cake and more, in ADDITION to the cheeses, breads, and antipasti. Will definitely be going back
One of my favorite restaurants in the world!  The creativity and hospitality this place delivers is tremendous.
Always a great restaurant for special occasions. Quiet, intimate, and well-prepared meals with a good selection of fair-priced wines.
You can climb to the top

I walked past the place 3 times before I found it. Hint: look for the Obelisk... Not complaining at all; bit adds to the place. Great food, and despite the fancy feel, you're free to wear shorts, you're free to dig in to the quail with your hands, you're free to be yourself and enjoy your dinner. Great experience.

Excellent food, good service, intimate setting.  Prix fixe Italian themed artisanal restaurant. I give only four stars because there seems little or no flexibility for food aversions; "We can always remove an ingredient."  Perhaps a call before hand would help avoid disappointment.  Everything worked out for us in the end and we spent three hours savoring the price fixe with the wine pairing ($78 per person on our visit).
Wonderful dining experience and the staff is knowledgeable anf courteous.

Excellent food from the antipasti all the way to dessert, served professionally in a quiet, low key ambiance.  If I could give Obelisk five and a half stars, I would.

All I can say is that I've lived in DC since 2003 and have eaten at scores of local restaurants... and the dinners I've had at Obelisk have been my favorites. It's cozy, the food is excellent, and the service is fantastic. People tend to forget about it because it doesn't do edgy cuisine, but it's not stuffy or boring; it's warm, welcoming, and always leaves you with a smile on your face. They just execute so, so well. Perfect fancy-yet-relaxing date night spot.
Haven't been here in years. So glad to see that the food, service and atmosphere are still at the top of the restaurant scale.

Most amazing food, wine and service! This restaurant is more of an experience rather than your regular restaurant. Rotating choice of items on the menu depending on what's available seasonally or what the chef has decided to present. Service is impeccable, bread is amazing especially the grissini. Presentation of the plates were spectacular and the wine list is very nice. The pasta course was delightful and just what pasta should be and the entrees are imaginative. Beautiful, cozy dining room. A must go of you can get reservations which are required.
The burrata and rest of the antipasti was amazing. Loved the bread and squash ravioli as well. The wine pairing pours were a little light but the overall meal was well worth the price!
Delicious food, great hosting, friendly relaxed atmosphere.

Great space, great staff, and delicious italian culinary ideas anchored by fresh local ingredients.

We visited Obelisk for a second time and, honestly, were nervous that it would fall short based on some of the other Yelp reviews.  WE LOVED our second experience even more than our first!  What a lovely and wonderful meal.  We visited for a special occasion....and it was indeed special!  Service was spot on and the food was simple, delicious and memorable....every.single.course.  Thank you, Obelisk!
Excellent food. Menu changes daily. Loved the handmade pasta I had here.
Obelisk is our favorite restaurant for special occasions.  The multi-course, country Italian menu changes daily.  Food is delicious & unique with surprises between courses and outstanding service.

"Sorry, but we can't accommodate strict vegans"  Does Obelisk not require its kitchen staff to receive culinary training or...  Seriously, if I can feed myself every day then the chefs working ar one of DC's most revered dining establishments should be able to cook a vegan meal when given proper notice.  Sorely disappointed.
Intimate and unpretentious experience with menu changing daily. Excellent with wine pairing.

My husband had fed me well for every special occasion. For his 30th (and since I do finally have a grown up job), it was my turn to return the favor.  I chose Obelisk after learning their tasting menu changes daily. It was a risky choice since i didn't have a clue what would appear on their menu that day. We went in keeping our fingers crossed hoping that they were serving attractive options. And we definitively were not disappointed!  Antipasti - smoked swordfish, grilled stuffed sausage, grilled pepper, fried fish, and burrata. I wasn't a big cheese fan to begin with (I actually asked if I could swap the cheese course for something else) but their burrata was a life changer! Soft, creamy, and light - I ate two whole breadbasket with smear of their scrumptious burrata alone!  Primi - arugula ravioli and spaghetti with clam - both pasta dishes could had been a meal on their own. Definition of perfectly made pasta!  Secondi - bass and quail. My husband enjoyed his bass but didn't think it was too memorable. He wasn't a big fan of the slaw salad pairing. I, on the other hand, picked up my whole quail and attempted to eat every piece of meat off the bone. Tender, juicy - out of the world!  Cheese - I'm so glad they said no to swapping my cheese course. I initially was just going to take a small bite of each but ended up polishing my plate clean! The hazelnut berry jam was the perfect compliment!  Desserts - chocolate chestnut cake and rosa pudding. The cake was nutty and moist but wasn't sweet enough - perhaps should had been paired with some type of ice cream or sweeter cream? My rosa pudding was really runny and didn't have the consistency of a pudding. It was also overwhelmingly sweet - what a contrast to their cake.  Overall - attractive, ever changing menu - perhaps we just came on a bad night for their desserts. Most of the dishes nevertheless were something I would definitely return for more! Service was a bit of a miss - we placed our order prior to the group of 6 next to us but they were served a whole course before us. We sat around for 25 minutes between each course. Our servers were not apologetic and offered no explanation. Ultimately, our 5 course dinner took over 3 hrs. Perhaps it was because we didn't order wine...  4 stars for food, 3 stars for service - Bad service really spoil dining experience! In sum 3.5 stars.

This will forever be one of my favorite restaurants in DC. I have had two unforgettable meals here, with many courses and incredible wine. Even the "simplest" of dishes is done exquisitely. Great place for a special occasion!

The best food I've ever had. From the cheeses to the main course and to the dessert. Everything was well seasoned and the service was impeccable. As a foodie, I was highly impressed and I will be back for more.

Located not too far from the heart of Dupont Circle, Obelisk is a true treasure find in Washington. A five-course Italian tasting menu reveals fantastic dishes with artistic performances. The parade of antipasti, pastas, and desserts makes this restaurant one of the most authentic, elegant, and flavorful in DC. The menu changes daily, but the top notch attentive service and dressy casual romantic intimate nature of the restaurant are forever the same. Located in a brownstone, the restaurant seems almost residential with close and cozy tables and it feels like you're inside someone's tasteful living room. There is limited seating so definitely make reservations.  Unlike other upscale restaurants with five course meals that seem more like one course meals, Obelisk's five courses are surprisingly very, very filling. The antipasti alone feels like an entire dinner, so I recommend you pace yourself when eating. Pastas are the restaurant's strength, but the meat and fish dishes are just as impressive. Obelisk is prix-fixe at $75 and there is a wine pairing option.  The restaurant has been around for 26 years and has been consistently known as DC's top Italian place for more than two decades, an impressive feat in the ever-changing culinary world. I came here with my boyfriend and close friends to celebrate his birthday and everyone loved the food, the drinks, and the atmosphere. It was such a perfect evening and we were all stuffed afterwards!

Obelisk gets one of my coveted "Best Evers" because it might be the best meal in DC.  It's a fixed price meal and they just keep bringing you small plates of food until your main course, which you pick from a menu.  You need to call right at 10am exactly a month before the night you want to go to ensure you can get a reservation.

Loved it. Doesn't look like a restaurant from the outside but honestly the food and service were fantastic. The only negative is that the room lacks a little atmosphere - all forgiven for the food and service. Friendly, knowledgeable and just unexpected.
excellent in every way.
still shines and strong
